obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12489)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12489&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Scheduled Tribes and`
  line `Other Traditional Forest Dwellers (Recognition of Forest Rights) Act, 2006.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. 31st December, 2007, vide notification No. S. O. 2224(E), dated 31st December, 2007, see Gazette of India Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec 3(ii)`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12490)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12490&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) ''community forest resource'' means customary common forest land within the traditional or`
  line `customary boundaries of the village or seasonal use of landscape in the case of pastoral communities,`
  line `including reserved forests, protected forests and protected areas such as Sanctuaries and National`
  line `Parks to which the community had traditional access;`
  line
  line `(b) ''critical wildlife habitat'' means such areas of National Parks and Sanctuaries where it has`
  line `been specifically and clearly established, case by case, on the basis of scientific and objective criteria,`
  line `that such areas are required to be kept as inviolate for the purposes of wildlife conservation as may be`
  line `determined and notified by the Central Government in the Ministry of Environment and Forests after`
  line `open process of consultation by an Expert Committee, which includes experts from the locality`
  line `appointed by that Government wherein a representative of the Ministry of Tribal Affairs shall also be`
  line `included, in determining such areas according to the procedural requirements arising from subsections`
  line `(1) and (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) ''forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes'' means the members or community of the Scheduled`
  line `Tribes who primarily reside in and who depend on the forests or forest lands for bona fide livelihood`
  line `needs and includes the Scheduled Tribe pastoralist communities;`
  line
  line `(d) ''forest land'' means land of any description falling within any forest area and includes`
  line `unclassified forests, undemarcated forests, existing or deemed forests, protected forests, reserved`
  line `forests, Sanctuaries and National Parks;`
  line
  line `(e) ''forest rights'' means the forest rights referred to in section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) ''forest villages'' means the settlements which have been established inside the forests by the`
  line `forest department of any State Government for forestry operations or which were converted into`
  line `forest villages through the forest reservation process and includes forest settlement villages, fixed`
  line `demand holdings, all types of taungya settlements, by whatever name called, for such villages and`
  line `includes lands for cultivation and other uses permitted by the Government;`
  line
  line `(g) ''Gram Sabha'' means a village assembly which shall consist of all adult members of a village`
  line `and in case of States having no Panchayats, Padas, Tolas and other traditional village institutions and`
  line `elected village committees, with full and unrestricted participation of women;`
  line
  line `(h) ''habitat'' includes the area comprising the customary habitat and such other habitats in`
  line `reserved forests and protected forests of primitive tribal groups and pre-agricultural communities and`
  line `other forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(i) ''minor forest produce'' includes all non-timber forest produce of plant origin including`
  line `bamboo, brush wood, stumps, cane, tussar, cocoons, honey, wax, lac, tendu or kendu leaves,`
  line `medicinal plants and herbs, roots, tubers and the like;`
  line
  line `(j) ''nodal agency'' means the nodal agency specified in section 11;`
  line
  line `(k) ''notification'' means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(l) ''prescribed'' means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) ''Scheduled Areas'' means the Scheduled Areas referred to in clause (1) of article 244 of the`
  line Constitution;
  line
  line `(n) ''sustainable use'' shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (o) of section 2 of`
  line `the Biological Diversity Act, 2002 (18 of 2003);`
  line
  line `(o) ''other traditional forest dweller'' means any member or community who has for at least three`
  line `generations prior to the 13th day of December, 2005 primarily resided in and who depend on the`
  line `forest or forests land for bona fide livelihood needs.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this clause, ''''generation'''' means a period comprising of`
  line `twenty-five years;`
  line
  line `(p) ''village'' means--`
  line
  line `(i) a village referred to in clause (b) of section 4 of the Provisions of the Panchayats`
  line `(Extension to the Scheduled Areas) Act, 1996 (40 of 1996); or`
  line
  line `(ii) any area referred to as a village in any State law relating to Panchayats other than the`
  line `Scheduled Areas; or`
  line
  line `(iii) forest villages, old habitation or settlements and unsurveyed villages, whether notified as`
  line `village or not; or`
  line
  line `(iv) in the case of States where there are no Panchayats, the traditional village, by whatever`
  line `name called;`
  line
  line `(q) ''wild animal'' means any species of animal specified in Schedules I to IV of the Wild Life`
  line `(Protection) Act, 1972 (53 of 1972) and found wild in nature.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12491)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Forest rights of Forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes and other tradional forest dwellers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12491&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) For`
  line `the purposes of this Act, the following rights, which secure individual or community tenure or both, shall`
  line `be the forest rights of forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes and other traditional forest dwellers on all forest`
  line `lands, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) right to hold and live in the forest land under the individual or common occupation for`
  line `habitation or for self-cultivation for livelihood by a member or members of a forest dwelling`
  line `Scheduled Tribe or other traditional forest dwellers;`
  line
  line `(b) community rights such as nistar, by whatever name called, including those used in erstwhile`
  line `Princely States, Zamindari or such intermediary regimes;`
  line
  line `(c) right of ownership, access to collect, use, and dispose of minor forest produce which has been`
  line `traditionally collected within or outside village boundaries;`
  line
  line `(d) other community rights of uses or entitlements such as fish and other products of water`
  line `bodies, grazing (both settled or transhumant) and traditional seasonal resource access of nomadic or`
  line `pastoralist communities;`
  line
  line `(e) rights including community tenures of habitat and habitation for primitive tribal groups and`
  line `pre-agricultural communities;`
  line
  line `(f) rights in or over disputed lands under any nomenclature in any State where claims are`
  line disputed;
  line
  line `(g) rights for conversion of Pattas or leases or grants issued by any local authority or any State`
  line `Government on forest lands to titles;`
  line
  line `(h) rights of settlement and conversion of all forest villages, old habitation, unsurveyed villages`
  line `and other villages in forests, whether recorded, notified or not into revenue villages;`
  line
  line `(i) right to protect, regenerate or conserve or manage any community forest resource which they`
  line `have been traditionally protecting and conserving for sustainable use;`
  line
  line `(j) rights which are recognised under any State law or laws of any Autonomous District Council`
  line `or Autonomous Regional Council or which are accepted as rights of tribals under any traditional or`
  line `customary law of the concerned tribes of any State;`
  line
  line `(k) right of access to biodiversity and community right to intellectual property and traditional`
  line `knowledge related to biodiversity and cultural diversity;`
  line
  line `(l) any other traditional right customarily enjoyed by the forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes or`
  line `other traditional forest dwellers, as the case may be, which are not mentioned in clauses (a) to (k) but`
  line `excluding the traditional right of hunting or trapping or extracting a part of the body of any species of`
  line `wild animal;`
  line
  line `(m) right to in situ rehabilitation including alternative land in cases where the Scheduled Tribes`
  line `and other traditional forest dwellers have been illegally evicted or displaced from forest land of any`
  line `description without receiving their legal entitlement to rehabilitation prior to the 13th day of`
  line `December, 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980), the`
  line `Central Government shall provide for diversion of forest land for the following facilities managed by the`
  line `Government which involve felling of trees not exceeding seventy-five trees per hectare, nemely:--`
  line
  line `(a) schools;`
  line
  line `(b) dispensary or hospital;`
  line
  line `(c) anganwadis;`
  line
  line `(d) fair price shops;`
  line
  line `(e) electric and telecommunication lines;`
  line
  line `(f) tanks and other minor water bodies;`
  line
  line `(g) drinking water supply and water pipelines;`
  line
  line `(h) water or rain water harvesting structures;`
  line
  line `(i) minor irrigation canals;`
  line
  line `(j) non-conventional source of energy;`
  line
  line `(k) skill upgradation or vocational training centres;`
  line
  line `(l) roads; and`
  line
  line `(m) community centres:`
  line
  line `Provided that such diversion of forest land shall be allowed only if,--`
  line
  line `(i) the forest land to be diverted for the purposes mentioned in this sub-section is less than`
  line `one hectare in each case; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the clearance of such developmental projects shall be subject to the condition that the`
  line `same is recommended by the Gram Sabha.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12492)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Recognition of, and vesting of, forest rights in forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes and other traditional forest dwellers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12492&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, and subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government hereby recognises and vests`
  line `forest rights in--`
  line
  line `(a) the forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes in States or areas in States where they are declared as`
  line `Scheduled Tribes in respect of all forest rights mentioned in section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the other traditional forest dwellers in respect of all forest rights mentioned in section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) The forest rights recognised under this Act in critical wildlife habitats of National Parks and`
  line `Sanctuaries may subsequently be modified or resettled, provided that no forest rights holders shall be`
  line `resettled or have their rights in any manner affected for the purposes of creating inviolate areas for`
  line `wildlife conservation except in case all the following conditions are satisfied, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the process of recognition and vesting of rights as specified in section 6 is complete in all the`
  line `areas under consideration;`
  line
  line `(b) it has been established by the concerned agencies of the State Government, in exercise of their`
  line `powers under the Wild Life (Protection) Act, 1972 (53 of 1972) that the activities or impact of the`
  line `presence of holders of rights upon wild animals is sufficient to cause irreversible damage and threaten`
  line `the existence of said species and their habitat;`
  line
  line `(c) the State Government has concluded that other reasonable options, such as, co-existence are`
  line `not available;`
  line
  line `(d) a resettlement or alternatives package has been prepared and communicated that provides a`
  line `secure livelihood for the affected individuals and communities and fulfils the requirements of such`
  line `affected individuals and communities given in the relevant laws and the policy of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(e) the free informed consent of the Gram Sabhas in the areas concerned to the proposed`
  line `resettlement and to the package has been obtained in writing;`
  line
  line `(f) no resettlement shall take place until facilities and land allocation at the resettlement location`
  line `are complete as per the promised package:`
  line
  line `Provided that the critical wildlife habitats from which rights holders are thus relocated for purposes of`
  line `wildlife conservation shall not be subsequently diverted by the State Government or the Central`
  line `Government or any other entity for other uses.`
  line
  line `(3) The recognition and vesting of forest rights under this Act to the forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes`
  line `and to other traditional forest dwellers in relation to any State or Union territory in respect of forest land`
  line `and their habitat shall be subject to the condition that such Scheduled Tribes or tribal communities or`
  line `other traditional forest dwellers had occupied forest land before the 13th day of December, 2005.`
  line
  line `(4) A right conferred by sub-section (1) shall be heritable but not alienable or transferable and shall be`
  line `registered jointly in the name of both the spouses in case of married persons and in the name of the single`
  line `head in the case of a household headed by a single person and in the absence of a direct heir, the heritable`
  line `right shall pass on to the next-of-kin.`
  line
  line `(5) Save as otherwise provided, no member of a forest dwelling Scheduled Tribe or other traditional`
  line `forest dweller shall be evicted or removed from forest land under his occupation till the recognition and`
  line `verification procedure is complete.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the forest rights recognised and vested by sub-section (1) are in respect of land mentioned`
  line `in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 3 such land shall be under the occupation of an individual or`
  line `family or community on the date of commencement of this Act and shall be restricted to the area under`
  line `actual occupation and shall in no case exceed an area of four hectares.`
  line
  line `(7) The forest rights shall be conferred free of all encumbrances and procedural requirements,`
  line `including clearance under the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980), requirement of paying the`
  line `'net present value' and 'compensatory afforestation' for diversion of forest land, except those specified in`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(8) The forest rights recognised and vested under this Act shall include the right of land to forest`
  line `dwelling Scheduled Tribes and other traditional forest dwellers who can establish that they were displaced`
  line `from their dwelling and cultivation without land compensation due to State development interventions,`
  line `and where the land has not been used for the purpose for which it was acquired within five years of the`
  line `said acquisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12493)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Duties of holders of forest rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12493&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The holders of any forest right, Gram Sabha and village level`
  line `institutions in areas where there are holders of any forest right under this Act are empowered to--`
  line
  line `(a) protect the wild life, forest and biodiversity;`
  line
  line `(b) ensure that adjoining catchments area, water sources and other ecological sensitive areas are`
  line `adequately protected;`
  line
  line `(c) ensure that the habitat of forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes and other traditional forest dwellers`
  line `is preserved from any form of destructive practices affecting their cultural and natural heritage;`
  line
  line `(d) ensure that the decisions taken in the Gram Sabha to regulate access to community forest`
  line `resources and stop any activity which adversely affects the wild animals, forest and the biodiversity`
  line `are complied with.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12494)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Authorities to vest forest rights in forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes and other traditional forest dwellers and procedure thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12494&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Gram Sabha shall be the authority to initiate the process`
  line `for determining the nature and extent of individual or community forest rights or both that may be given`
  line `to the forest dwelling Scheduled Tribes and other traditional forest dwellers within the local limits of its`
  line `jurisdiction under this Act by receiving claims, consolidating and verifying them and preparing a map`
  line `delineating the area of each recommended claim in such manner as may be prescribed for exercise of such rights and the Gram Sabha shall, then, pass a resolution to that effect and thereafter forward a copy of the`
  line `same to the Sub-Divisional Level Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by the resolution of the Gram Sabha may prefer a petition to the`
  line `Sub-Divisional Level Committee constituted under sub-section (3) and the Sub-Divisional Level`
  line `Committee shall consider and dispose of such petition:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such petition shall be preferred within sixty days from the date of passing of the`
  line `resolution by the Gram Sabha:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such petition shall be disposed of against the aggrieved person, unless he has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity to present his case.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall constitute a Sub-Divisional Level Committee to examine the`
  line `resolution passed by the Gram Sabha and prepare the record of forest rights and forward it through the`
  line `Sub-Divisional Officer to the District Level Committee for a final decision.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by the decision of the Sub-Divisional Level Committee may prefer a`
  line `petition to the District Level Committee within sixty days from the date of decision of the Sub-Divisional`
  line `Level Committee and the District Level Committee shall consider and dispose of such petition:`
  line
  line `Provided that no petition shall be preferred directly before the District Level Committee against the`
  line `resolution of the Gram Sabha unless the same has been preferred before and considered by the SubDivisional`
  line `Level Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such petition shall be disposed of against the aggrieved person, unless he has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity to present his case.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Government shall constitute a District Level Committee to consider and finally approve`
  line `the record of forest rights prepared by the Sub-Divisional Level Committee.`
  line
  line `(6) The decision of the District Level Committee on the record of forest rights shall be final and`
  line binding.
  line
  line `(7) The State Government shall constitute a State Level Monitoring Committee to monitor the process`
  line `of recognition and vesting of forest rights and to submit to the nodal agency such returns and reports as`
  line `may be called for by that agency.`
  line
  line `(8) The Sub-Divisional Level Committee, the District Level Committee and the State Level`
  line `Monitoring Committee shall consist of officers of the departments of Revenue, Forest and Tribal Affairs`
  line `of the State Government and three members of the Panchayati Raj Institutions at the appropriate level,`
  line `appointed by the respective Panchayati Raj Institutions, of whom two shall be the Scheduled Tribe`
  line `members and at least one shall be a woman, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) The composition and functions of the Sub-Divisional Level Committee, the District Level`
  line `Committee and the State Level Monitoring Committee and the procedure to be followed by them in the`
  line `discharge of their functions shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12495)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Offences by members or officers of authorities and Committees under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12495&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Where any`
  line `authority or Committee or officer or member of such authority or Committee contravenes any provision`
  line `of this Act or any rule made thereunder concerning recognition of forest rights, it, or they, shall be`
  line `deemed to be guilty of an offence under this Act and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any member of the authority or`
  line `Committee or head of the department or any person referred to in this section liable to any punishment if`
  line `he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised all due`
  line `diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12496)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12496&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence under section 7 unless any`
  line `forest dwelling Scheduled Tribe in case of a dispute relating to a resolution of a Gram Sabha or the Gram`
  line `Sabha through a resolution against any higher authority gives a notice of not less than sixty days to the`
  line `State Level Monitoring Committee and the State Level Monitoring Committee has not proceeded against`
  line `such authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12497)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Members of authorities, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12497&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the authorities referred to`
  line `in Chapter IV and every other officer exercising any of the powers conferred by or under this Act shall be`
  line `deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12498)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12498&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any officer or other employee of the Central Government or the State Government for anything`
  line `which is in good faith done or intended to be done by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government or any of its officers or other employees for any damage caused or likely to be caused by`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any authority as referred to in Chapter IV`
  line `including its Chairperson, members, member-secretary, officers and other employees for anything which`
  line `is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12499)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Nodal agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12499&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Ministry of the Central Government dealing with Tribal Affairs or any`
  line `officer or authority authorised by the Central Government in this behalf shall be the nodal agency for the`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12500)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12500&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `In the performance of its duties and exercise`
  line `of its powers by or under this Act, every authority referred to in Chapter IV shall be subject to such`
  line `general or special directions, as the Central Government may, from time to time, give in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12501)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Act not in derogation of any other law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12501&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act and the`
  line `Provisions of the Panchayats (Extension to the Scheduled Areas) Act, 1996 (40 of 1996), the provisions`
  line `of this Act shall be in addition to and not in derogation of the provisions of any other law for the time`
  line `being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12502)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238&sectionId=12502&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_42_71_00001_200702_1517807323238
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, and subject to the`
  line `condition of previous publication, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) procedural details for implementation of the procedure specified in section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for receiving claims, consolidating and verifying them and preparing a map`
  line `delineating the area of each recommended claim for exercise of forest rights under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6 and the manner of preferring a petition to the Sub-Divisional Committee under sub-section`
  line `(2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(c) the level of officers of the departments of Revenue, Forest and Tribal Affairs of the State`
  line `Government to be appointed as members of the Sub-Divisional Level Committee, the District Level`
  line `Committee and the State Level Monitoring Committee under sub-section (8) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the composition and functions of the Sub-Divisional Level Committee, the District Level`
  line `Committee and the State Level Monitoring Committee and the procedure to be followed by them in`
  line `the discharge of their functions under sub-section (9) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
